Wife loved her clam chowder and lobster roll. I got a pizza and onion rings. Neither were anything special but I blame myself for not getting steak tips with my choice of two sides. Before I forget... you may want to consider reservations. They open at 12 and we had a reservation for that time.  I couldn’t believe how many people were there for opening time. Wow! What an amazing place! This was my first time in the Boston area and friends highly recommended this place for food and drinks. I have a dairy allergy and the chef ensured the plate I wanted would be modified to perfection and the food was amazing!  Our waitress was super friendly! The staff was helpful in understanding the safety measures in place during the pandemic.  If you want a nice night out with friends or a date night, Scarlet Oak Tavern comes highly recommended by me.  This was a much needed night out with the pandemic transitioning to reopening. We had a lot of laughs, great food, and great staff that helped us really enjoy our night out.

We went for Valentine's Day. We had a reservation for 9:30 at night. As soon as we got there we were seated. The atmosphere was really nice and cozy. Beautiful old wood floors and comfortable booths. Each table has a butcher paper table cover with a [fake] candle, which adds some nice ambiance.  For starters, we got calamari and oysters as a starter. The calamari had a perfect crust, though there was a couple of the rings were a little too chewy, the majority of it was perfectly cooked. The sauce that was served with it was super flavorful, with a nice kick. Oysters were nice and fresh.  For entrees, I got the Lamb Chops and my boyfriend got the Hanger Steak Frites. The lamb was cooked to perfection & had a delicious arugula pesto on top. It was also placed on top of this cauliflower puree, which was so buttery and flavorful that I'm still thinking about. The dish also had sweet potatoes, which while flavored very well, seemed a little soggy. My partner liked his steak, it was cooked to a perfect rare, per his instructions. He said the frites, while good, got a little overwhelming afterr awhile due to the truffle oil. He also wished there was a sauce over the steak instead of the marrow butter.  Our waitress was incredibly nice and friendly. She clearly was working hard to make sure all of her guests were having a good experience.  It's a bit pricey, but if you have a special occasion and want delicious food, this is the place to go! Would love to come back!  Note: they have a complementary valet service; we did not use it, but it is nice they offer it.

My wife made reservations there for 6:30 to have Thanksgiving dinner. We arrived and we're promptly seated. We both ordered the turkey dinner. The server was great, she was pleasant and efficient. I had the crab cake and my wife had the bisque for our appetizer. They were excellent. The turkey dinner itself was terrible. My wife likes her turkey and chicken on the dry side, I like mine moist. Even she could not eat her turkey because it was so dry and tough. It was like chewing on cardboard. It was if the turkey came out of the oven in the morning and was under a heat lamp the whole day. The desert was supposed to be a warm chocolate type cake. It was stone cold. We still left a good tip for the server, bad food wasn't her fault. Will not be going back. I am giving this a one star because you expect more from a nice restaurant. I have had better at a road side diner.

Scarlet Oak Tavern has outstanding food....period.  it doesn't matter that tables are close, the food is incredible.  Usually when I go out to eat, I don't get food that I can make (expertly) at home, so steak, chicken, and most fish are not on my menu.  I look for the unique stuff any restaurant would offer, and I came across a risotto with scallops...simple, yes, but something I would not normally make at home.  The dish was amazing.  The wait staff was awesome.  Super attentive, but not over the top like some can be.  They made the dining experience perfect.  My son ordered a rare flank steak, which was perfectly executed.  My daughter selected a pan-seared tuna steak that was ridiculously well prepared.  Portions are very reasonable, so you feel satisfied and you aren't hauling food home.  Prices are also reasonable.  For a night out (this was birthday #47 for me), it's not a bad price point at all.  I highly recommend Scarlet Oak.  You won't be disappointed.
